Fargo Davies Eagles couldn't stop Grand Forks KnightRiders' winning run
The Fargo Davies Eagles and the Grand Forks KnightRiders met on Thursday, Jan. 29, 2025.
The Fargo Davies Eagles and the Grand Forks KnightRiders met on Thursday, Jan. 29, 2025.
Grand Forks came into the game off the back of a run of 10 successive wins and managed to claim yet another victory. The game finished 2-1.
ADVERTISEMENT
The first period was scoreless, and early in the second period, the KnightRiders took the lead when Taylor Kilgore scored assisted by Ella Yahna.
The KnightRiders increased the lead to 2-0, only 49 seconds into the third when Taylor Kilgore found the back of the net again, assisted by Dustee Balek and Chloe Groven.
The Eagles narrowed the gap to 2-1 early in the third period when Anika Astrup beat the goalie, assisted by Kyndal Sheeley.
Coming up:

The KnightRiders will take on the Eagles in the next game on Tuesday, Feb. 04, 2025 at 1 p.m. CST at Burdick Arena.
